  "prompt": "Is white an actual color?",
  "response": "Whether white is considered a color can depend on the context in which you're discussing it.\n\n1. **In Physics**: White is not a color in the same way that pigments are; rather, it's a combination of all colors of light. When light contains all wavelengths of visible light in roughly equal intensities, it appears white. For example, sunlight is made up of many colors, and when separated by a prism, it can create a spectrum of colors.\n\n2. **In Art and Pigments**: In terms of pigments and paints, white is often considered a color, as it can be used to create shades and tints of other colors. When mixing pigments, white reflects most light and can lighten other colors.\n\n3. **In Everyday Language**: People commonly refer to white as a color in day-to-day conversations regarding design, fashion, and art.\n\nSo, the classification of white as a color can vary based on personal, scientific, or practical perspectives.",
